    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Distill documents with PostgreSQL and Outlook\n\n**Pattern:** AI Summarize & Route · **Level:** Production · **Trigger:** Webhook\n\n## What it does\nDistill documents with PostgreSQL and Outlook. It fires the moment an external system calls its webhook.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual q&a is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nReceive Inbound Webhook → Keep Valid Documents → Classify with AI → Store as Action Needed → Reunite Branches → Stamp Completion Time → Persist Run Metadata → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to ai summarize & route without manual effort\n- Anyone automating q&a in ai\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Improves response time\n- Scales without extra headcount\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2 / service account; Microsoft OAuth2; OpenRouter API key; Postgres connection.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "0ac563e0-2f1d-e98d-2756-a43faf672c6a",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -500
      ],
      "id": "ebaa40ed-4111-f92a-d63f-53907f7a0112",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🔐 Security\n\nNever trust inbound payloads: the webhook path is unguessable. Add header auth or IP allow-listing for defense in depth. Secrets live in n8n credentials — never in node parameters.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        190,
        -500
      ],
      "id": "24f8a5ac-4ec7-4f93-e129-e46b92673c66",
      "name": "🔐 Security"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 6
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        610,
        -500
      ],
      "id": "36e0401f-1c4d-af0f-fdba-be55b0794df9",
      "name": "🤖 AI cluster"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your q&a process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 4
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
